

All tests assume readelfobj (version to test)
is copied to this directlry by PICKUP
or something else

test objects named
comprelad32.x  comprelal32.x  comprelat32.x	compstrtab.x
comprelad.x    comprelal.x    comprelat.x	compsymtab32.x
comprelaf32.x  comprelar32.x  compshstrtab32.x	compsymtab.x
comprelaf.x    comprelar.x    compshstrtab.x	hello32.x
hello.x
were built by 
cc -c hello.c -o hello.x
or
cc -c -m32 hello.c -o hello32.x

The other tests were created from these objects

changeone() {
    sec=$1
    oname=$2
    echo "======== $1 $2"
    eu-elfcompress -f -o $2 -n $1 hello.x
    echo "$rotest $2 "
    $rotest $2 | grep $1
}
changeoneb() {
    sec=$1
    oname=$2
    echo "======== $1 $2"
    eu-elfcompress -f -o $2 -n $1 hello32.x
    echo "$rotest $2 "
    $rotest $2 | grep $1
}

changeone .strtab   compstrtab.o
changeone .symtab   compsymtab.x
changeone .shstrtab compshstrtab.x
changeone .rela.text comprelat.x
changeone .rela.debug_info    comprelad.x
changeone .rela.debug_aranges comprelar.x
changeone .rela.debug_line    comprelal.x
changeone .rela.eh_frame      comprelaf.x

changeoneb .strtab   compstrtab32.o
changeoneb .symtab   compsymtab32.x
changeoneb .shstrtab compshstrtab32.x
changeoneb .rela.text comprelat32.x
changeoneb .rela.debug_info    comprelad32.x
changeoneb .rela.debug_aranges comprelar32.x
changeoneb .rela.debug_line    comprelal32.x
changeoneb .rela.eh_frame      comprelaf32.x





